##Pearl River Delta Survey: SHORT-TERM SHORTAGE OF RAW MATERIALS, long-term supply chain relocation

Weixin caijingEleven

HIGHLIGHTS:

1. Over the past decade or so, the Pearl River Delta has developed a supply chain model that is unique in the world. From screws and metal structures to chips, hundreds of suppliers are linked like Lego blocks into a web.

2. More than 60 percent of China's electronics processing companies operate in Pearl River Delta, and most automated production lines require more than 80 percent of their employees to be in place to run.

3. In order to encourage the new and old employees to come to the production line as soon as possible, Foxconn Longhua campus has introduced a relatively attractive system of starting bonuses in batches: Starting before March 31, starting 60 days to pay 4,250 yuan, starting 90 days to pay 2,500 yuan, that'll be $6,750.

4. In order to save the emergency, the practice of most enterprises is to concentrate the existing staff in some conditions to run up the production line. Many of the company's management personnel also temporarily under the line, temporary replacement of labor.

5. For supply chain companies, the impact from the economic downturn, industrial restructuring and trade frictions between China and the United States is far-reaching compared with the epidemic.

6. Combining the observations of several supply chain companies, most international manufacturing giants used to look for two suppliers in the same country to hedge against risk. The trend is for one product to have a separate supplier in each country.

7. The advantage of having supply chains in both places is that capacity can be quickly moved overseas if the domestic market is affected, and vice versa. There should be product hedging, market hedging, customer hedging, and even business model hedging to offset the negative impact.

"If we slow down, it's dangerous, " Tan Honglin, a marketing manager at Taobang screw, told CAIJING. The dongguan-based screw maker received a call from Swedish customers on February 10, the day it resumed work. The message is clear and can be replaced if the response is not quick enough.

This is the Pearl River Delta most export-oriented manufacturing enterprises back to work day scene. Topol screws has 60% of its customers overseas, after the outbreak of new crown pneumonia, the domestic manufacturing industry in the short term to press the pause button. But these overseas customers continue to produce, they are most concerned about the suppliers after the resumption of delivery capacity.

During the first few days back at work, the staff responded to customer emails almost every second of the day. Huang Qi, general manager of a Metal Structure Company in Shenzhen, told Caijing that not only will every customer do a re-work investigation, but also different departments will make phone calls, and a link will be repeatedly confirmed many times.

According to "finance and Economics" reporters understand that the entire Pearl River Delta region, these export-oriented manufacturing enterprises to resume the earliest, the test is also bear the brunt. On the one hand to meet the requirements of overseas customers, on the other hand, as a result of February to squeeze orders, cash flow has been tested. If you don't deliver on time, some of your blood will come under pressure in April or May.

The recovery of the whole supply chain is slower than expected, the resumption of work has begun, the resumption of production also needs a mediation period.

"Back to work means you can open the door, like a movie theater. One person is back to work. But you may not be able to guarantee production, " Huang said. Next, not only is the completion rate of personnel, material inventory can keep up, will be the test of the Pearl River Delta Enterprises Key.

WE CAN'T BE EFFICIENT IF we're not all together

The Pearl River Delta is a major region for migrant workers, with 26 million migrant workers in Guangdong province alone, coming from all over the country. The return of people is also slower than in other areas because of traffic control in many places.

Huang's company also has a factory in Suzhou, which is not a labor-importing city. Most of the workers are local. Nearly 100 employees have arrived two weeks after returning to work. But at the company's Shenzhen plant, only a few dozen workers have been hired so far.

More than 60 percent of China's electronics processing companies are based in the Pearl River Delta, and for Labor intensive companies, capacity depends on how many workers show up on time. In fact, most automated lines require more than 80 percent of their employees to be in place to run. "A radish a pit, the link on the production line is continuous, less people can not open up, " said Huang Qi.

Foxconn, which relies mainly on automated production lines, is stuck in a labor shortage. As of February 28, the resumption rate at the Longhua campus of Foxconn in Shenzhen was 30 percent, and "the production line is basically half-open, " a director of the facility told Caijing, each division-level cadre has the head task, must recommend an ordinary employee to go to work in the factory. There is a bonus for completion, but completion does not affect performance.

In order to encourage the new and old employees to come to the production line as soon as possible, Foxconn Longhua campus has introduced a relatively attractive system of starting bonuses in batches: Starting before March 31, starting 60 days to pay 4,250 yuan, starting 90 days to pay 2,500 yuan, that'll be $6,750.

On the other hand, sometimes we're all here, and we can't do it without the key people. This is especially true for production lines that require an engineer level presence at all times. "The engineers themselves take up a position on the production line, and if there is a shortage, even if the rest of the staff is all there, the line will not go on, " Huang said.

By "CAIJING" reporter investigation, most of the Pearl River Delta enterprises to the personnel in mid-late March can be complete. In order to save the emergency, the practice of most enterprises is to concentrate the existing staff in some conditions to run up the production line. Many of the company's management personnel also temporarily under the line, temporary replacement of labor.

From February 17, Huang Qi's Shenzhen plant, from factory managers, managers and office staff are personally on the production line, overtime shipment, just to return a little cash flow. But because the office staff is not familiar with the movement, the whole line down, the efficiency is not high.

Cai Huabo, chairman of Shenzhen Jiangbolong Electronics Co. , told Caijing that due to various restrictions, even if the personnel reached 70% , the current efficiency can only return to 30% of normal. However, Cai believes that many enterprises are now mainly concerned about the problem of staff arriving at their posts, and a month later, the shortage of raw materials may be the biggest challenge.

Solve the problem of material shortage

Shenzhen Jihecheng Technology Co. , Ltd. is a manufacturer of Industrial Control Computer (IPC) enterprises. The company's senior director Liu Yun told CAIJING, although chips, motherboards and other core components of the stock is more adequate, not too worried. But there could be a shortage of structural parts, and "you can't ship a computer without a part, " Liu Yun said.

Manufacturers of structural parts are also worried about supplies of raw materials. The shaft produced by Huangqi Company is a structural part, mainly used in office equipment such as printer, whose main material is plastic and processed metal. The main suppliers also have their own downstream suppliers, such as steel mills, which he worries about whether they will be able to produce in time.

According to "CAIJING" reporters understand, many of the Pearl River Delta Stainless Steel Plant, special materials plant to complete supply to April. But Huang Qi only has enough materials in stock for one month. Now, I wake up every morning, I call my supplier, and I stock up as soon as I can.

This is also the inventory status of most enterprises in the Pearl River Delta. Inventory means that part of the cash flow into fixed assets, Liu Yun told Caijing, spare parts have safety inventory indicators, for example, motherboard inventory cycle is generally 1 to 2 months.

For most consumer electronics industries, the cycle is shorter because the product changes too quickly. "Last month's product requirements may change this month, and parts will have to be replaced, " an OEM for European and American customers told Caijing that small and medium-sized electronics assemblers are almost afraid to stock up. But now due to the lack of components, difficult to resume production.

Many in the industry believe that the current supply chain is not exposed to obvious problems, because everyone is still digesting inventory. Once the inventory is used up, and too late to replenish, is the time of the test.

Over the past decade or so, the Pearl River Delta has developed a supply chain model that is unique in the world. From screws and metal structures to chips, hundreds of suppliers are linked like Lego blocks into a web.

A Ricoh Printer has more than 700 parts, 95% of which are made in the Pearl River Delta. Liu Yun told Caijing that the company's raw material purchases are concentrated in Pearl River Delta.

Theoretically speaking, the more detailed division of Labor, the higher efficiency and greater flexibility in coordination, which is the advantage of the Pearl River Delta Model. But once there is a problem, the whole network to restore operation is also relatively complex.

This is because supply is chain-like, cut-off supply is chain-like. "even if I don't lack raw materials, if my partner lacks spare parts, there will still be problems overall, " Cai told CAIJING.

Once out of stock, it is not easy to change the material supplier. According to Liu Yun, it would take at least two to three months to develop a new motherboard, including evaluating materials and pre development, validation, and testing.

This means that the supply of any one component, for the entire industry chain, can be fatal. The hoarding of raw materials has already occurred. But the ability to stock up on enough goods still depends on cash flow and reserves of resources, at which point the giants have an absolute advantage.

According to "CAIJING" reporters understand that a large factory directly locked a memory chip manufacturers a whole production line. The memory chip was one of Liu Yun's suppliers. "That is to say, it is impossible for this factory to supply US small companies any more. " So the company had to turn to other suppliers.

Some of the components agents are intended to "cover goods. ". Still taking memory chips as an example, Samsung is the world's largest manufacturer of memory and flash memory chips, while SK Hynix is the world's second largest memory manufacturer, some chip resellers in the Pearl River Delta are playing hard to get, and Liu Yun says memory chips are also priced at one a day.

Accelerating overseas distribution of supply chain

While supply chains have been hit, most companies still think the impact will be short-term. According to the reporter from Caijing, since late February, most cities in the Pearl River Delta, including Dongguan, have started to implement the policy of first resuming construction and then auditing. On the other hand, with the liberalization of traffic control in various places, the pace of resuming work and production is obviously quickening.

According to the Guangdong Provincial Department of Human Resources and social security, as of February 21,45.5 percent of enterprises in Guangdong had resumed work, of which 49.7 percent were among 988 key employers. A number of PRD companies are optimistic that supply chains could recover to 80 per cent by April.

Wang Hong, general manager of Tuobang screws, told CAIJING that for supply chain companies, the impact from the economic downturn, industrial restructuring and sino-us trade friction is the most far-reaching compared with the epidemic.

In fact, some big multinationals are already adjusting their supply chain strategies. Over the past year, as a result of sino-us trade frictions, there has been a consensus that all eggs can not be put in one basket and that the supply chain needs to be flexible enough to respond to any possible international developments. Now the outbreak has accelerated that process.

Tan told Caijing that the outbreak had prompted his Swedish clients to set up a dedicated team to rebuild overseas supply chains for components such as die-casting and plastic parts. According to "CAIJING" reporters understand, including Canon, brothers and other Japanese manufacturers are also willing to accelerate the change of their supply chain pattern.

Combining the observations of several supply chain companies, most international manufacturing giants used to look for two suppliers in the same country to hedge against risk. The trend is for one product to have a separate supplier in each country.

This means that after the outbreak, how to better adapt to the new industrial pattern, improve the self-competitiveness of supply chain enterprises is the more core issue.

Cai Huabo believes that the ability of supply chain enterprises to accelerate overseas distribution will be a major trend. In fact, the company had previously placed 60 per cent of its capacity overseas because of the risks. Since the outbreak, the company's overseas factories have not been affected based on foreign supply chains, offsetting some of the losses at home.

The advantage of setting up supply chains in both places is that, "If the domestic market is affected, you can quickly move capacity overseas and vice versa. There should be product hedging, market hedging, customer hedging and even business model hedging to offset the negative impact,"he told Caijing.

In the changing international situation, multi-point flowering is undoubtedly an important means to enhance the overall competitiveness. Huang Qi told CAIJING that the company has domestic competitors, but because it has factories in Vietnam, upstream manufacturers have not changed suppliers despite the difficulty in scaling up production capacity.
